A Food Safety Roundtable heard that the recent Listeriosis outbreaks are only the tip of the iceberg. The outbreaks affected other countries such as Australia, but South Africa experienced the highest number of deaths.  
Food borne diseases like Listeriosis can have devastating consequences for both manufacturers and consumers, including loss of lives. 
At the Roundtable organised by food giant Mondelez South Africa in Johannesburg, experts heard that the country is not immune to another outbreak. Thabile Mbhele reports... --SABC--